trend_summary: From earliest to latest imagery the built-up footprint grows outward and inward: industrial estates thicken on the north, housing and commercial blocks fill former fields east and centre, and a wider highway grid appears. A southwest quarry expands while roadside tree belts and park vegetation rise slightly, sustaining a balanced but increasingly urbanised suburban landscape.
notable_changes: Northern industrial zone gains several large white-roof warehouses and parking lots.
Vacant fields east of the central spine are replaced by compact residential/commercial blocks.
South-western quarry pit enlarges and adds a new spoil or water pond.
New arterial road segments and roundabouts strengthen the radial-ring network.
Incremental tree planting along corridors and parks raises visible green cover.
